---
title: Chicken & Brussels Ricotta Flatbreads with Parmesan & Italian Cheeses
description: In our humble opinion, flatbreads are a level above pizza! We know that may sound crazy, but stick with us. The golden crust is a blank canvas, not beholden to simply marinara and mozz! In fact, ours is topped with herby lemony ricotta, shredded Brussels sprouts, melty cheeses, lemon zest, and a drizzle of hot honey. Can your ’za do that?! Yeah, we didn’t think so.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66156042d0360c342f04b478-547474e9.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67b464282ccb8b03ddc11e0d-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-and-brussels-ricotta-flatbreads-67b464282ccb8b03ddc11e0d
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 910 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 58 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1060 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and
preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Lay flat and thinly slice
crosswise into shreds.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking Oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add Brussels sprouts; season with @Italian Seasoning{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4
servings) and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. (You'll use
more Italian Seasoning in the next step.) Cook, stirring occasionally, until
bright green and softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Open package of @chopped Chicken Breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess
liquid; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of
cooking Oil{} in a separate large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken
or sausage and cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}.

While Brussels sprouts cook, zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Ricotta Cheese{4%ounce}, half the lemon zest,
@Italian Seasoning{1/2%tsp} (be sure to measure—we sent more), and a squeeze
of lemon juice to taste. (For 4 servings, use 3/4 of the lemon zest and 1
tsp Italian Seasoning.) Stir in @olive Oil{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Place @Flatbreads{2} on a #baking sheet{}. Brush or rub each with a drizzle of
olive Oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toast on top rack until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide
flatbreads between 2 baking sheets; toast on top and middle racks,
swapping rack positions halfway through baking.)

Carefully spread toasted flatbreads with lemon ricotta. Top with Brussels
sprouts in an even layer. Sprinkle with @Italian Cheese Blend{1/2%cup} and
half the @Parmesan Cheese{1%tbsp} (save the rest for serving).

Bake on top rack until cheese melts and flatbreads are crispy,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Top flatbreads with chicken or sausage along with Brussels sprouts.

Cut flatbreads into pieces.

Divide between plates and drizzle with @hot Honey{1/2%ounce}. Sprinkle with
remaining Parmesan and remaining lemon zest to taste. Serve with any
remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.